or undefined line over which
presidents shouldn't go?

06:07.433 --> 06:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW DOWD: Well, Americans
expect our president to be human
beings, and as imperfect as all

06:13.766 --> 06:15.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of us are.

06:15.033 --> 06:17.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They expect us to make
mistakes and all that.

06:17.033 --> 06:20.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But one thing the American
public likes is, if you make a
mistake, you do that, you cross

06:20.533 --> 06:25.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that line that they expect
you to behave under,
then you apologize or
then you correct that

06:25.100 --> 06:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
behavior and said you have
learned, you are going to do
better, you are going to achieve

06:28.233 --> 06:30.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
better, and you are
going to serve a higher
purpose than that.

06:30.800 --> 06:34.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Let's keep in mind that
Donald Trump didn't
win because of himself.

06:34.866 --> 06:37.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He won in spite of himself.

06:37.400 --> 06:41.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A quarter of his voters
voted for Donald Trump
believing he wasn't
presidential and he didn't

06:41.400 --> 06:46.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have the temperament, but they
had hope that he would grow
into the office and become more

06:46.033 --> 06:48.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
presidential.

06:48.100 --> 06:51.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That doesn't seem to have
happened, and I don't think it
will happen for a 71-year-old

06:51.100 --> 06:53.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
man.

06:53.133 --> 06:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Beverly,
you know, apropos of what just
Matt just said and what you said

06:55.133 --> 06:59.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a moment ago, clearly, there
are moments when presidents
have grown angry, they have been

06:59.166 --> 07:01.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
upset because they
have been criticized.

07:01.633 --> 07:06.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So is there some kind of
standard, written or otherwise,
for how a president is to speak

07:07.366 --> 07:09.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the American people?

07:09.366 --> 07:13.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEVERLY GAGE: I don't think
there is a written standard,
but I think up until this moment

07:13.400 --> 07:18.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
there have been some
sort of accepted norms
that the president in
particular -- on the

07:19.566 --> 07:21.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
campaign trail, it's
one thing, right?

07:21.633 --> 07:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is a place where people
attack each other when they have
differences of opinion or maybe

07:25.300 --> 07:27.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
even personal attacks
in that venue.

07:27.533 --> 07:29.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is sort of expected.

07:29.100 --> 07:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There, Trump took it to a
new level as well, I think.

07:32.833 --> 07:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when you are the president,
the idea that you cannot rise
to the office, that you would

07:39.800 --> 07:42.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
